This past Sunday night my husband and I decided to try this place because it was close to our hotel. We placed a reservation through Open Table for 7:30pm. We walked along the river walk until we came to the restaurant, but was met with a blockaid that said "dead end" and told by a group of drunk people on the patio (who turned out to be employees) "you can't come in here."  We assumed they meant that we had to walk around to the other entrance, so we took the 10 minute hike all the way down by the street and street car tracks.  We were once again met with a dead end.  I called the restaurant and the very nice man on the line said that they were closed INDEFINITELY.  and they had only found out about 3 hours prior.  I think that says something as to what kind of people run this place.  I'm more curious to know why this place has not been marked as closed yet on Google???

The gator was not as expected. Guess that's our fault. Then, watched them put a cluster of snow crab in the "hand sink only" sink and ran water on it. Just visited here 2 days ago, based on the amount of great reviews my husband and I had read- we were really excited to try this place! He grew up in New Orleans so is no stranger to good seafood.. but after eating there we both agreed it was an extremely disappointing dining experience... To begin with, he ordered a lobster (his favorite food) and it came out so fast that we were impressed, and curious about HOW it came out so fast.. then when he took a bite of it, it was very apparent his lobster was already cooked and was re heated. hands down the toughest and most horribly seasoned seafood we have EVER had in New Orleans! Aside from that, I ordered the étouffée which is a staple for me every time we visit the city, and I have never had a bad étouffée in New Orleans, until eating here.. it was just all around bad quality seafood, especially for the price. I wish I could say something positive about the experience, but even the cleanliness of the establishment was HORRENDOUS! I took my 4 year old to the restroom and as soon as we opened the door we were literally SLOSHING around in water on the floor.. or, we HOPE it was water and not sewage leaking as it had all sorts of debris, toilet paper, etc floating around in the puddles... I honestly do not even know how a restaurant (even in New Orleans) can stay open with that kind of presentation for its guests. SAVE YOUR MONEY, and your time, and go somewhere else!!!

My wife really wanted to go here as she loves seafood and had high hopes despite the poor reviews in many places online (google, tripadvisor, yelp, ect.).  From the second we walked in, we quickly realized that all the poor reviews were 100% accurate and that this place has some serious service and management problems.  We were there at 4pm and of course the restaurant was not really busy.  We were seated in the outside covered area where the window coverings were all rolled down making the whole area feel like a sauna - just a build up of hot, humid, stagnant air.  I figured I just ask the waitress to roll them up when they came to our table.  Problem was, they never came to our table.  We waited there for 15 minutes without anyone ever coming with menus, waters, ect.  While waiting I watched a server woof down a bunch of food in plain view of the dining area and then went on to wait on a table without washing her hands.  I also saw 3 other staff just leaning against a wall loudly talking, doing nothing.  I've worked in food service for a total of 17 years of my life, from expensive restaurants to small time pizza places and I have never witnessed such atrocious service on a number of levels.  Whoever is in charge of this place should be immediately fired because it is clear that there is no standards or accountability.  The fact that my review is not an isolated incident shows that despite a long track record of problems, management or ownership has done nothing to rectify the problems.  In a city where there is so many awesome places to eat, this place is not worth your money or frustration.  After 15 minutes we walked out.  The sad part was I don't think any employees noticed that either or if they did they didn't care.  We then walked over to the Gumbo Shop near Jackson Square and had one of the best meals of the trip with impeccable service.  I should have just went with my gut and went there to begin with.

It's like eating in the center of the pre-katrina projects...like who hires some of these people. While making a complaint to the manager about how rude my waitress was, this ghetto girl with a plastic weave glued onto her head was just standing there laughing in my face. I paid her no mind because  I know how they like to fight and I'm never o.k. with violence. I tried to handle it nicely by first letting my waitor know that I was dissatisfied with service, he didn't take it very well so I asked for his manager. He then yelled at me... "go tell her, she right ova dea!!! Tell whoever you want!!!" (In front of the entire restaurant) I was appalled, to say the least... I swear I thought he would hit me. I disengaged immediately. I then asked a man standing next to him at the register to please get me a manager. He pointed and said "she right over there just go walk up, she'll talk to you." Me:    ☠... Crazy thing is the general manager was there. I spoke to her and the manager. They both apologized but it was almost like this was the norm. The general manager said that she would talk to him immediately.... I was so confused...in my head I'm like... talk to him??? He just yelled at me...at that point, I knew it was hopeless. I still plan on contacting corporate just to inform them of the experience and to let them know how their brand is taking a good dragging by the people they chose to hire. There are a couple more jawdropping incidents during this visit but after this book i just wrote, this is all the energy I can spare for now...As good as that mahi sandwich was, I will never go back...but if you still choose to go after this review, get the GROUPON so you don't feel too bad about the🗑service. #corporatecleanhouse

Buyer beware!!!  Now I know why they have a groupon for this. Worse dining experience is not even enough to describe how bad it was. I went here for a date night with my husband. We had to wait for more than 10 min for a waiter to come to our table and it wasn't even a busy time, there were only a few customers in the restaurant. The menu was a bit confusing to us as some of the pricing was not clear. We finally decided to get the lobster salad and bourbon street combo.  After a while, the band started playing and we our table was so close to them that we can't hear each other talking. The band wasn't there when we were seated and the waiter didn't mention anything about it, nor did he bother to care ask us if we want a different table when we told him how loud the band is and how we have difficulty hearing one another because of this.  Finally the food came. The portion was small definitely not worth the price they ask for. Not only that, you have to do everything by yourself. The lobster in the lobster salad is not mixed in with the veggies. It's just served in its shell so we have to dig it out ourself, which wasn't easy because the lobster was tough and rubbery (I've never had lobster that tough, even in cheap place) it even made my jaw sore chewing it. The veggies in the salad was only iceberg lettuce (the cheapest kind), a shaving of carrot that was barely there, tomato, and 2 little slices of green pepper. The lobster salad was not the only "DIY" project during our dining time. The shrimp in the bourbon street combo was not peeled so we had to peel it ourselves. And yes, the shrimp was also tough. To top it off, we asked for the lobster salad to be delivered first (as it was an appetizer) but they brought all the food all at once. So there we were, struggling to mix our lobster with the veggies while our main course was getting cold.  Finally after we were done eating, it took a while for the waiter to come and take our payment. So my husband went to (what seemed like ) the cashier. The lady told him that we could only do payment through our waiter. Not a big deal, but still additional negative thing after everything we went through. Turned out she was the manager. My husband tried to tell her about the issues we were having and instead of trying to rectify the situation, she was being aggressively defending the situation. Not even a single apology for all the issue we had. So much for a customer service attitude!  Never again will I come here! Bad food, way overpriced, bad service. Nothing is good about this place!!!
The worst experience ever. Service sucked and took way longer than should have. I will never come back

The seafood here was great! I ordered crab legs and shrimp, and it came with some corn, sausage and potatoes. Lots of meat in the crab legs and super tasty. The service was also great and my waitress was awesome! Definitely got a taste of some southern hospitality and I will be coming here again the next time I visit NOLA!

Service and food were great. We had a large group and didn't feel like a burden on the staff. Boiled seafood buckets, boiled shrimp, lobster, mussels, clams, sausage, corn and potatoes.. All Good. The "Category 5" Hurricane was a strong as it should be. Live band was also pretty good.
Germika did an excellent job. I'd recommend this place just because of her service. Thanks again!
Definitely the food was not worth the money ! Lobster meet was very chewy.
Love it
Great food and love the outdoor seating
Great food great service,  a little pricy but worth it, the view is beautiful.
We come here every time were in town - great grilles Oysters and good atmosphere. Always leave very full and happy Keep it up Crazy Lobster J&J
Dissatisfied with my visit. Got the surf and turf. Lobster was overcooked; rubber. Steak was fatty and grisly with nothing in the way of flavor. Great view and location though.

We found the service to be quite good. Destini, our server, was very attentive and made sure we had everything we needed.  Meanwhile, my girlfriend and I ordered the Bounty of the Sea -- lobster, crab, shrimp, mussels, clams, sausage, corn, and potatoes. I'm not an expert on seafood and thought everything was good, but my girlfriend is more particular about her seafood and was in food heaven and thoroughly enjoyed everything.
Recommended by my Uber driver...nice place the Cajun Calamari was delicious highly recommend it
Good food butna bit pricey
Great food, great atmosphere right on the waterfront with live music. Get the Voodoo Juice! Table service could have been a little more polite and attentive.
The shrimp Cajun boil was outstanding. Service was perfect. Waiter helped is out like a tour guide explaining the menu.
Food was good.
Food is always  delicuous! Staff is very upbeat  and restaurant always clean. One of my favorite spots to come.

(Translated by Google) Poor food. Everything from the fries. Fat and salty. Lemonade is water with juice. High prices  (Original) Jedzenie kiepskie. Wszystko z frytury. Tlusto i slono. Lemoniada to woda z sokiem. Ceny wysokie
The place is rather dirty. meal was fat and salty.
Pricy but excellent food! Chad, our server, was fantastic. Great live music.
Buckets of seafood is extremely filling and best shared. We usually get the lobster or two...come hungry if you do as it is A LOT of tasty seafood. I am not kidding...come hungry.
Used a Groupon. The food was good as were the wait staff. Would definitely come here again.
The food was very good, not to spicy. The price was right. Not to much, just the right amount. We love the Berboun seafood with crab legs.
Love love everything food,service and drinks wish I could give it more stars
The food Boiled Seafood Combo for $33.was worth every dollar. Our waitress Ms.Troy was really cool. Enjoyed the location. They simply need to spruce the place up some.

Lazy and unfriendly waitress. Food wasn't special. The tips were included in the bill 20% mandatory! And we agreed that she deserved nothing. Don't eat here. Worst place we've been on our 3 weeks trip.

My dad and I went for the 2016 Sugar Bowl and stumbled upon this place. The waitress was very friendly and funny, but the atmosphere seemed a bit off. Probably because the weather was very cloudy and the wind was cold as can be. The porch area wasn't very warm, but the food (I had Shrimp and Grits) was hot and delicious. Dad ordered Red Beans and Rice and some other side, and he said he loved it. Sad to see all the bad reviews.

Our problems started right at the check-in counter.  We asked for a table for 10 and immediately went and added more.  The woman at the desk snapped at me and couldn't have seemed more annoyed.  Though it looked half empty, it took over 30 minutes to seat us.  After sitting down, we ordered bottled waters and bottled beer....and it took over 20 minutes to receive them.  Food came out faster than we thought it would after the drink fiasco, but when it came time to get the checks, oh boy.  The server agreed to split them, though it's against their policy, but it's as if she totally forgot about it.  45 minutes to get the check?  And oh yeah, do you remember the woman from check in?  Turns out she's a manager who wasn't managing anything.  She did nothing to help us get checked out faster, and the only time she seemed to care was when we started to leave having never received the bill.  Rather than apologizing, she fought with multiple guests in our party.  All in all, a 2+ hour ordeal and headache was NOT a good start to our vacation.  Terrible customer service, and NO professionalism from the "manager."
The seafood buckets are on the pricey side, but they are very nicely done. Sometimes the service is a little hit or miss. Very touristy.

The gumbo was a joke,the crab cakes were imitation, the gator bites were not real gator meat. This place needs to be shut down immediately. They keep mayonnaise outside all-day on the tables inside and out..who does that.
Great tasting seafood, beans and rice and shrimp Po boy. Great service, place could be cleaner, overall not bad.
Food is s*it and it was too expensive! The bathroom smelled better than the restaurant it's self! Disgusting!
The food was horrible and the prices are too high. The restaurant smells like a grease trap. I will not eat there again and don't recommend it.

Worst experience..first time in New Orleans,first stop was to this place. We where talked into ordering steam bowl and then when bill came out..it was $120 although under description there was a $38 amount. But when we questioned prices and asked for itemized receipt we where doubled charged for bowl and then charged for clams and mussels which we did not order and to top it off we ordered a cup of gumbo which we did not get until 5 min before we left and was not even charged for gumbo but some other appetizers for 7 bucks..waitet claimed this was the way they had to bill??? it was a mess and we did not want to make a big scene . Then waiter said we should be happy because we had a coupon..we did not even get a copy of receipt, maybe because waiter gets 20% gratuity off the top!! Will never go there again dishonest staff !! Travelers beware😠
This place is kind of a touristy spot. But the food is still pretty good. You can get a large variety. It's also nice to have all of the outdoor seating when the weather isn't too hot.

Came here at 11am. Our waitress was Katie, she was so sweet and accommodating. My daughter and I had the  Lobster pasta and gator bites, both were delicious. It was a little expensive, so I am glad I had a Groupon. However I would come back when in NOLA again.
Food is good, the view is great. We enjoyed eating here, but we also had a good coupon. I can see it getting out of hand...

Food was good, service was OK. Our waiter was prompt and friendly but was noticeably stressed/irritated and almost got into a physical fight with another coworker in front of the entire restaurant. The reason for 2 stars is that we ordered ice waters and the waiter said the water had just got turned back on and he wasn't sure if it was clean and recommended we get bottled water or a soft drink, to which my husband replied, wouldn't all the fountain drinks and ice be dirty too? And the waiter had no real response. He brought us ice waters and the ice had black stuff on it. In all 4 cups. We didn't touch our drinks and by the end of the meal the black stuff had settled to the bottom of the cups. The inside of the restaurant had a bad smell too. Only went because of a groupon.
Nice location, good service. Drinks and food are a little bit expensive.

The atmosphere at the Crazy Lobster was very nice. The music on the porch was not so loud that you could not have a nice lunch conversation. There was a soft breeze coming off the Mississippi River. When our lunch was brought: an alligator po-boy and a catfish po-boy, we were so excited! The food portions were generous, fresh, and hot a trifecta on the restaurant world. I would be remiss is I did not mention that we were welcomed by every employee when we entered the crazy lobster, and the manager also came by to welcome us and thank us for coming. Nice touch.

Horrible please don't go.... Food was really bad.....lot's of mosquitoes, overpriced and dirty. I ordered the crawfish for which i was given the dish with small prawns. I was told that these are crawfish????? Really bad experience.The seafood bucket was for $98 what a joke

The WORST dining experience I have had in a very very long time.  The waitress begged off when I asked her about the signature drinks.  She brought out 4/5 entrees and left us for several minutes with no silverware. Finally she brought silverware and walked away when I tried to ask about the 5th meal. the table next to us went unbussed for 30 minutes.  we waited  30 minutes for our check. we were never offered new drinks, checked on to see if our bland cold food was acceptable. STAY AWAY

Stop, DO NOT GO HERE!!!!!  Oh where do I begin.  First, we had to wait for a hostess as she was busy talking with her friends, then she walks to the stand, no acknowledgement, she simply picked up two menus and walked away, and then after she walked away she looked back with a mean face like we were stupid and should have known to follow her, we were seated without her saying a word.  We were seated in fact by the General Manager John and his family, and had the pleasure of watching him and his family enjoy multiple waiters and heaping plates of food.  While we waited for service.  After 30 min a waitress approached us and asked us if we had been waited on, we said no, and she said she wasn't sure if we were her table, she left and came back 10 min later and apologized and said she was our waitress.  We ordered drinks and off she went, 10 min later she was back with drinks, Be aware you will pay for water, 2.00 per bottle.  The bloody mary $14.00 was drinkable but nothing special.  We then ordered our entree's I ordered the Crawfish ettouffee and my fiance ordered a bowl of gumbo and the taste of new orleans which was Jambalaya, Etouffee, and redbeans.  Listen I cant stress this enough we grew up on the gulf coast we understand how Gumbo and the other dishes are supposed to taste, if your not from the area you have no idea, so to you it might be good, but let me tell you the food was horrible, the etouffee had no flavor and the gumbo's roux was watery and again had no flavor. The rest of the food was simply not good.  We had purchased a groupon for this place and that included a dessert and so we ordered the bread pudding, again it was horrible, it was tough and rubbery.  That was it, we had had it, so we asked to speak with John the general manager, 20 seconds into our conversation he basically dismissed us and said dont worry ill take care of the meal, while that was generous that wasn't really what we wanted to hear, we continued to try and explain our issues, he then got extremely rude, explained that he was the GM for a multi million dollar operation and if things were that bad, the restaurant wouldn't make it, I disagree, they have a fantastic location on the river in the riverwalk center, and there are plenty of unaware tourist that pay his bills.  He even told me to contact the owner that he would tell me the same thing.  I have yet to do so but im curious as to what his response will be.  The only pleasure I received from the meal was watching countless customers get up and walk out after not receiving service and the fact that I personally was able to turn away 2 groups saving them from a horrible experience.  Take my warning to heart, bad food, bad service, bad management.

Not sure why the bad reviews but this place was great, atmosphere was good with live band and a view, service was excellent not sure if you can ask for a waiter but Isaih B. Did a great job attending us. Food was pricey but that's expected for good food 👌
Great waiter. Food was taking a little while and he gave us an order of complimentary fries. A little tourist trap like but the food was good and the drinks were strong so it's forgiven.

SERVICE SUCKS waitress never made rounds for refills or ofeered had to ask an since we had more than 5 people she know she had a tip already an made no effort to help. If the plae was on fire i forget the phone num er to 911 this place is terrible.

While the hostess was nice our waiter was horrible. He didn't bring condiments when asked multiple times. He brought a plastic cup of lemonade that leaked all over. After yelling for his attention, he finally brought a towel. The etouffee was bland and the jambalaya was cold. The gumbo was good. I will never be back.

The Jambalaya and gumbo were okay but other items were bland. We were seated in front of dirty dish bin and our server did not checked on us, not a single time.  However, they charged auto gratuity of 20 percent. Would never recommend.
The food was excellent & the waiter was also!!!
Poppy's voodoo juice yummio big time, loved the food, waitress was funny, and enjoyed food by the water it's a great place for real Gump seafood
Crawfish Étouffée was delicious, service was great but the food is a little overpriced.
It was pretty good. I got the seafood bucket and ate the whole thing!
Great spicy snow crab legs that were delicious! My boyfriend and I had the bourbon street tea which was amazing, and had good service. We will probably be back before returning to Texas!
Horrible service from the waiter staff . I can go to corner store for better service. Won't be back .
Cozy setting located right on the Mississippi.  Oysters on the half paired with their awesome Bloody Mary drinks and it was a great day.

The hostess was rude when we walked in,  but the worst part was an crazy lobster employee stole our umbrella. I caught him in the rain, took it back,  and went to see the manager. All she had to say was I don't know why he would do that,  sorry.  Worst experience ever......

Great location. Food definitely subpar. I ordered the shrimp and grits. Plenty of shrimp but the execution lacked and the tender let it sit under the heat lamp too long.  The bar was understaffed for a Sunday
Great seafood .had lobster pot. Even have those silly drinks

You can sit outside or inside, whatever you choose.  We went during lunch, so it wasn't busy at all.  It was very quiet and we sat outside and had a beautiful view of the Mississippi River.  It's also in a very nice location-lots to see around the area.  Also, the waiter was very friendly and even tied my bib around my neck for me, lol.  The food was very good, too-great seafood and great cajun food for which the city is known.
An overpriced nasty tourist attraction. I would never eat here again.
Food was ok. Way too overpriced and the waitress basically vanished on us.
Well, I was planning to visit this place, but the reviews leave me quite nervous! Have they changed management and staff in the last year?

Ate here twice while visiting and both had an excellent service experience and delicious food. The BBQ shrimp po boy was excellent, as was the crawfish etouffee and the gourmet cheeseburger. They were very generous with the crawfish on the etouffee, unlike some other locations we ate at. The burger was far better than I expected, very juicy, flavorful, and cooked exactly as ordered. They also have pretty great battered fries. The Voodoo Juice is an awesome drink by the way! Tasty and quite strong and the refills on the 600ml souvenir cup are only $8!
Fish tacos are yummy.
Excellent service and the food delicious

This place was definitely fun. Our waiter was great,  attentive and fun. We got the infamous voodoo juice (which is extremely strong..) Along with jambalaya and the lobster. They were both great minus the lobster being 47.99... We used their Groupon. The only bad thing with the Groupon was that it couldn't be used on the seafood bucket, which is what they are famous for. However,  overall a fun touristy experience on the water.

The food was great! Service was fast and everything was just what we wanted. The waitress gave us free refills on soda and even split our check without us asking. Had a live band playing and was in a great location on the water. Had no wait at all and we got there around 9pm on a Friday.  Ionly gave 4 stars due to we had to pay 20% surcharge for a group of 5. I would go again though
Portions were huge, service and quality were eh

Was there last night. Place was not too crowded, but had to wait 20 minutes to be seated. After being seated for 30 minutes and no one coming to our table. We walked out. There is no one in charge there. The neon sign doesn't work either. You should take that as a sign of the place in general.

My wife and I were looking for a nice dinner just a bit out of the craziness of St. Patties' day, we found the Crazy Lobster on the 19th of march, We had the 2lb lobster, crawfish, muscles, shrimp, and oyster bucket. Without question one of the most fantastic dinners we have had in a while. This is not to say, the prices were cheap, but very reasonable for the quality and quantity of the feast. I would recommend this restaurant to anyone visiting new Orleans. Great food, excellent service, and nice views of the Mississippi river traffic. She and I have traveled a good deal for business across this country back when the corporate credit card was still my friend. We could not remember a better experience. Crazy Lobster is going to be the new high water mark for us. Thanks!
Plenty of food, reasonably priced, good taste, great wait staff.

Stopped at the Crazy Lobster on Sunday morning before the Mystic Krewe Of Barkus parade.  The band was awesome as was the entire staff...  I ordered Oysters on the Half Shell.. They were fresh and large...  Very tasty.  I also ordered the Cajun Mary.  A version of the Bloody Mary, but turned up a notch...  Very, very good....

It hurts me to write this review because there were some very nice people at this restaurant.  My sisters and I went to this restaurant for dinner 3 times while I was in New Orleans.  The food was great each day.  I am rating it a one because of the service received by our waitress named Regina.  She was horrible and very rude.  We were not given utensils for our seafood or bibs.  No water. And when asked she got upset and mocked my sister as if she was talking to a complaining child.  She was throwing things down on the table and just outright nasty.  She came to our table several times asking for our checks before we even finished our food.  I am sure that this behavior was because of the mandatory 20% tip that was automatically added to our bill.  I finally had had enough and asked for the manager.  The manager Ashley Smith was just as rude and openly intimidated by Regina who snatched our ticket from Ashley's had and went over to the cash register to cash our ticket our.  We were asking that the tip not be paid to Regina because of the service we had received, but it was too late because she cashed the ticket out.  There were two other tables that had the same issue with Regina and asked for manager assistance.  At first Ashley refused to come out and speak with the guest, but because they refused to sign their receipts until she came..she came out.  One lady said she would only sign if her tip went to the other waitress who helped her even though it was not his table.  And the other lady wanted the tip taken off her bill.  This was the worst experience anyone should have to endure.  I asked was there anyone over Ashley that we could speak with and was told no.  It was obvious that Ashley could not handle the staff and someone else should have be present.  Would not recommend do to staffing issues, however the food was great.  And the other two nights the staff was great.

Out of towners - you can't drive here! Personal experience after over an hour of driving. Park nearby wherever your gps takes you. Food was good. I can see where people say the wait staff is rude but decent food would definitely go back

We liked the cozy, friendly interior and attentive and helpful wait staff. Seafood Platters (fried) were the entrees ordered ($24.99), with a side salad ($4.99), which was much better than average. The seafood platters had fried oysters, fried shrimp, fried catfish, hush puppies, a delicious crab cake, and French fries. We all thought the items on the platter were very good, and we were unable to find anything that was lacking. Portions were generous, and the childrens' plates came it little paper fishing boats, and they were thrilled about that. We received two free tasty bread puddings when we promised to post written reviews online. I would strongly recommend this place. RJT

We had the BEST grits ever here in a a dish they call Shrimp and Grits. It was so creamy and flavorful - and the shrimp were perfection. Huge portion that two could have shared. The prices are good, too! We recommend this place right on the riverfront to anyone wanting a nice view and great food! I should mention the service was VERY good as well. We'll be coming back again.

Their seafood is nasty from the crawfish to the crab and lobster.  Their service leaves much to be desired.  Their establishment is not clean; be careful going to the restrooms to not slip on the greasy floor and try not to touch anything in the bathroom.  However they do make amazing fried pickles.
Manager lady bad tude. Take the fly swater green flies as big as giant bates trying to rape food.
Food served abudantly. Decor is cool. Something for everyone. Try the oyster and spinach with raspberry dressing. Just one of my favorites.

Had a $25 for $50 off deal from Groupon. We had their version of a Hurricane (Pat O'Briens was stronger). Wife had the shrimp & grits, I ate the lobster & steak. My meal was seasoned and cooked really well (steak medium). The shrimp & grits were edible but not really flavorful. Our sever was a bit slow but overall ok. We told him we eat Gluten Free yet he kept bringing us bread. While my meal was good I wouldn't go back w/o a discount of some sort. Way too overpriced.
Not a bad place, but pricey for the quality. Service was great.
Total tourist trap. Just awful. Lobster was chewy! And the service... what service?

Food is terrible tourist trap not a single dish is authentic. Don't waste your money if you have a living social deal buy drinks only every food item on menu is disgusting. 18$ for terrible shrimp jambalaya, 9$ for shrimp cocktail that was bland and tasteless and included 5 shrimp with peels still on. Pass this place doesn't have a clue about New Orleans food or food in general. yuk is best descriptive word.

Location, location, location. That's all this place has and it probably gets by on that alone. Why even try when you're guaranteed enough tourists to pay the bills. Food was mediocre at best and prices were not in line with the quality. Service was poor because they did not have enough wait staff. Go elsewhere. You're in NOLA and there's not shortage of better places.
Waiter messed up order. Ate my appetizer for dinner. And even that wasn't any good.
I love their food. Crab cake PO boy is amazing!

A bit on the high end, but well worth it! A cool place to sit in or outdoors on the pier outside of the French quarter.  Great selection, generous portions, this food was delicious! A real taste of New Orleans

There is something enchanting about sitting on the banks of the great Mississippi River watching old riverboats and trawlers go by, eating fresh seafood plucked from the Gulf hours ago, and sipping local brewed beer. Throw in a couple of local musicians, a couple hundred drunk tourist, and a Crazy Lobster and there is Mardi Gras.  Cajun Popcorn Crawfish battered, and fried to perfection, seasoned with Cajun spices. Delightful little pops of swamp mud bugs. The batter was light and crisp, a crunchy carrier for the muddy swamp bugs which tasted very fresh and plumb. Crab cake, crabmeat blended with seasoned bread crumbs, battered and fried, served with remoulade sauce. This was all crabmeat and very little bread crumbs. There was crab in every bite. Jambalaya a Louisiana tradition. Shrimp, chicken, and Cajun sausage smothered with Cajun spices and rice. The rice was moist and shrimp and chicken fresh. The sausage was perfectly seasoned and cured.  A dozen fresh shucked oyster came on ice. I wondered if the shucker reached out the back window and caught these oysters? Fresh, plumb, and huge, these oysters would make New Orleans proud. Abita Purple Haze was the perfect adult beverage to accompany this meal.  Amazing scene, live, active, loud, friendly, great food, great beer, warm service, winds from the giant old river…….welcome back New Orleans, welcome back.
